{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dd030534-e481-4ed9-9b1a-bfe80575dd8d","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically when you save a file\n- **`--filter`** — only run tests matching the filter, so just your single test\n\nYou can also filter by the shorter display name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nNow every time you edit and save, only that one test will re-run.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5f50a4dd-6ff8-4e90-b3b3-b7417d069832","outputTokens":157,"requestId":"CFCE:1BCB52:6178F7C:6D17E6D:69EC1A40"},"id":"54ba60a6-6c75-4135-9ace-3ede4ca6c520","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:35:02.306Z","parentId":"39da931b-e17a-4d03-8754-696fbc47b264"}
